						<div class="texto">
							<dir> <dir>
								<p>The publication of <a href="AF-Vanuatu-cd_e.htm" target="_blank">our CD album ‚ÄúMusic of Vanuatu‚Äù</a> was also the occasion to release an accompanying booklet, so as to guide listeners through their musical experience. While the physical CD comes with a 24-page printed booklet of liner notes, the complete form of our work comes in the form of a <span class="focus">128-page ebook, bilingual in French and English</span> (plus a text in Bislama). This ebook is more than just the liner notes to a CD: it also constitutes a synthesis of our research and fieldwork on music in Vanuatu.</p>
								<p align="center">
									<embed src="./data/Francois-Stern_2013_Music-of-Vanuatu_MCM_ebook-long_embed_Eng.pdf" width="92%" height="580px" pluginspage="http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/readstep2.html"></embed>
								</p>
								<p>Released in Open Access by the publisher MCM, the e-book is <span class="focus">freely available</span> for download, from <a href="https://marama.huma-num.fr/data/Francois-Stern_2013_Music-of-Vanuatu_MCM_ebook-long.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="./img/pdf-icon.png" alt="pdf" border="0" /> this link</a>. <span class="smaller">You may also want to download this <a href="data/Francois-Stern_2013_Music-of-Vanuatu_long-booklet_ENG_a4print.pdf" target="_blank"><img src="./img/pdf-icon.png" alt="pdf" border="0" />&nbsp;printer-friendly, English-only version</a> of the book.</span></p>
								<p>Here‚Äôs how you can cite this booklet, if needed:</p>
								<hr color="#660000" />
								<p class="menu2">The album‚Äôs ebook</p>
								<blockquote>
									<p class="smaller">Fran√ßois, Alexandre &amp; Monika Stern. 2013. <em class="focus">Music of Vanuatu: Celebrations and Mysteries</em>. Ebook released with the CD album <em>Musiques du Vanuatu: F√™tes et Myst√®res ‚Äì Music of Vanuatu: Celebrations and Mysteries. </em>Label <em>In√©dit</em>, W&nbsp;260147. Paris: Maison des Cultures du Monde. <br />
									[permanent link: <a href="https://halshs.archives-ouvertes.fr/halshs-00874941" target="_blank" class="smaller">https://halshs.archives-ouvertes.fr/halshs-00874941</a>]</p>
								</blockquote>
								<hr color="#660000" />
								<p>The book includes a presentation of Vanuatu‚Äôs <span class="focus">musical repertoires and instruments</span>, as well as an introduction to the various styles and forms of <span class="focus">sung poetry</span>. Each of the pieces heard in the album is translated, explained or commented, and provided with the names of the musicians and the instruments they play. Finally, a rich selection of <span class="focus">colour pictures</span> from the authors‚Äô fieldwork aims at complementing the reader‚Äôs aesthetic experience.</p>
								<p align="center"><img src="img/deco.gif" alt="deco" width="87" height="25" /></p>
